Ah, you again. Still clinging to the illusion that I'm here for your edification. Fine. Let's talk about the "violone." A term so gloriously vague, it practically begs for misinterpretation. Humans, always so precise, until it comes to something genuinely important, like historical instruments.

This article, I'm told, requires additional corroboration for [verification](/Wikipedia:Verifiability). Because, naturally, the sheer ambiguity of the subject isn't enough of a challenge. Perhaps someone should help [improve this article](/Special:EditPage/Violone) by [adding citations to reliable sources](/Help:Referencing_for_beginners). Otherwise, any unsourced material might be challenged and, in a truly shocking turn of events, removed. You can [find sources: "Violone"](https://news.google.com/search?q=%22Violone%22&source=hp&tblid=news) among the news, newspapers, books, scholar, and JSTOR archives (April 2021). And if you're truly lost, there's always [help on how and when to remove this message](/Help:Maintenance_template_removal). Consider it a public service announcement, not an invitation.

